1
00:00:07,458 --> 00:00:09,625
Katara: WATER...

2
00:00:09,667 --> 00:00:11,291
EARTH...

3
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:13,500
FIRE...

4
00:00:13,542 --> 00:00:16,125
AIR.

5
00:00:16,166 --> 00:00:20,083
LONG AGO, THE FOUR NATIONS
LIVED TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

6
00:00:20,125 --> 00:00:24,458
THEN EVERYTHING CHANGED
WHEN THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

7
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:28,458
ONLY THE AVATAR,
MASTER OF ALL FOUR ELEMENTS,
COULD STOP THEM.

8
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:32,208
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST, HE VANISHED.

9
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:35,750
100 YEARS PASSED
AND MY BROTHER AND I DISCOVERED
THE NEW AVATAR...

10
00:00:35,792 --> 00:00:37,917
AN AIRBENDER NAMED AANG.

11
00:00:37,959 --> 00:00:40,250
AND ALTHOUGH HIS AIRBENDING
SKILLS ARE GREAT

12
00:00:40,291 --> 00:00:43,500
HE HAS A LOT TO LEARN BEFORE
HE'S READY TO SAVE ANYONE.

13
00:00:43,542 --> 00:00:46,959
BUT I BELIEVE AANG
CAN SAVE THE WORLD.

14
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,542
♪

15
00:00:55,417 --> 00:00:58,333
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT THIS WAR
HAS PUT ME THROUGH.

16
00:00:58,375 --> 00:01:00,041
ME PERSONALLY.

17
00:01:00,083 --> 00:01:03,333
THE FIRE NATION TOOK MY MOTHER
AWAY FROM ME.

18
00:01:03,375 --> 00:01:05,667
I'M SORRY.

19
00:01:05,709 --> 00:01:10,041
- YOU MIGHT HAVE EVERYONE ELSE
HERE BUYING YOUR TRANSFORMATION

20
00:01:10,083 --> 00:01:13,667
BUT YOU AND I BOTH KNOW
YOU'VE STRUGGLED WITH DOING
THE RIGHT THING IN THE PAST.

21
00:01:13,709 --> 00:01:17,208
SO LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING
RIGHT NOW.

22
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:22,250
YOU MAKE ONE STEP BACKWARD,
ONE SLIP-UP, GIVE ME ONE REASON
TO THINK YOU MIGHT HURT AANG

23
00:01:22,291 --> 00:01:25,208
AND YOU WON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT YOUR DESTINY ANYMORE.

24
00:01:25,250 --> 00:01:29,667
♪

25
00:01:29,709 --> 00:01:33,125
[BIRDS CHIRPING...]

26
00:01:35,750 --> 00:01:39,208
[SNORING]

27
00:01:42,583 --> 00:01:45,083
[YAWNS]

28
00:01:45,125 --> 00:01:47,041
[APPA GRUNTS]

29
00:01:50,583 --> 00:01:52,458
[APPA GROWLS]

30
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:16,125
Zuko: WATCH OUT!

31
00:02:16,166 --> 00:02:18,000
[GRUNTING]

32
00:02:18,041 --> 00:02:19,458
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

33
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,625
KEEPING ROCKS FROM CRUSHING YOU.

34
00:02:20,667 --> 00:02:23,834
OK, I'M NOT CRUSHED,
YOU CAN GET OFF ME NOW.

35
00:02:23,875 --> 00:02:25,667
I'LL TAKE THAT AS A THANK-YOU.

36
00:02:28,542 --> 00:02:30,750
COME ON, WE CAN GET OUT
THROUGH HERE.

37
00:02:30,792 --> 00:02:32,041
[MOMO CHATTERING]

38
00:02:32,083 --> 00:02:34,208
[GROANS] WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

39
00:02:34,250 --> 00:02:36,583
GO AHEAD, I'LL HOLD THEM OFF.

40
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:38,750
I THINK THIS IS A FAMILY VISIT.

41
00:02:38,792 --> 00:02:40,542
ZUKO, NO!

42
00:02:40,583 --> 00:02:43,709
COME ON, WE'VE GOT TO
GET OUT OF HERE.

43
00:02:57,542 --> 00:02:59,500
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

44
00:02:59,542 --> 00:03:02,083
YOU MEAN IT'S NOT OBVIOUS YET?

45
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:05,166
I AM ABOUT TO CELEBRATE
BECOMING AN ONLY CHILD.

46
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,709
[SHOUTS]

47
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:39,834
[APPA GROANS]

48
00:03:39,875 --> 00:03:41,542
Aang: I CAN'T GET HIM
TO GO IN THERE.

49
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:43,417
APPA HATES TUNNELS.

50
00:03:43,458 --> 00:03:46,208
AANG, THERE'S NO WAY
WE CAN FLY OUT OF HERE.

51
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:48,333
Aang: WE'LL HAVE TO FIND A WAY.

52
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:50,458
WE NEED TO SPLIT UP.

53
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,792
TAKE THE TUNNEL AND
GET TO THE STOLEN AIRSHIP.

54
00:03:52,834 --> 00:03:55,041
NO.

55
00:03:55,083 --> 00:03:58,166
THE FIRE NATION CAN'T
SEPARATE OUR FAMILY AGAIN.

56
00:03:58,208 --> 00:03:59,417
IT'LL BE OK.

57
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:00,709
IT'S NOT FOREVER.

58
00:04:16,834 --> 00:04:19,500
I CAN CLEAR THAT AWAY AND
WE CAN FLY OUT THROUGH THERE.

59
00:04:19,542 --> 00:04:23,208
UM, THERE'S AN AWFUL LOT OF FIRE
IN THAT GENERAL DIRECTION.

60
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:24,417
WE'LL GET THROUGH.

61
00:04:24,458 --> 00:04:25,417
LET'S GO.

62
00:04:28,041 --> 00:04:29,500
[APPA GROWLING]

63
00:04:40,166 --> 00:04:41,792
[MOMO CHATTERING]

64
00:05:02,458 --> 00:05:03,333
[APPA GROANS]

65
00:05:03,375 --> 00:05:05,083
[GRUNTS]

66
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:08,041
[APPA GROANING]

67
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:28,792
[GRUNTING]

68
00:05:30,417 --> 00:05:33,083
[GRUNTING]

69
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:37,333
[APPA GROANS]

70
00:05:41,375 --> 00:05:43,417
SHE'S NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

71
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:52,750
OF COURSE SHE DID.

72
00:05:52,792 --> 00:05:55,166
[APPA GROANS]

73
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,750
Aang: WOW, CAMPING...
IT REALLY SEEMS LIKE
OLD TIMES AGAIN, DOESN'T IT?

74
00:06:03,792 --> 00:06:07,083
IF YOU REALLY WANT IT TO FEEL
LIKE OLD TIMES, I COULD, UH...

75
00:06:07,125 --> 00:06:09,291
CHASE YOU AROUND AWHILE
AND TRY TO CAPTURE YOU.

76
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:10,458
[LAUGHTER]

77
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:13,208
HA-HA.

78
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:15,583
[SIGHS] TO ZUKO.

79
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:18,000
WHO KNEW AFTER ALL THOSE TIMES
HE TRIED TO SNUFF US OUT

80
00:06:18,041 --> 00:06:20,000
TODAY HE'D BE OUR HERO.

81
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:22,500
All: HEAR HEAR.

82
00:06:22,542 --> 00:06:23,875
I'M TOUCHED.

83
00:06:23,917 --> 00:06:25,208
I DON'T DESERVE THIS.

84
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:28,959
YEAH, NO KIDDING.

85
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,500
WHAT'S WITH HER?

86
00:06:30,542 --> 00:06:34,333
I WISH I KNEW.

87
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:36,125
Sokka: WHAT'S WITH HIM?

88
00:06:41,959 --> 00:06:43,917
THIS ISN'T FAIR.

89
00:06:43,959 --> 00:06:46,166
EVERYONE ELSE
SEEMS TO TRUST ME NOW.

90
00:06:46,208 --> 00:06:47,000
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU?

91
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:49,083
OH, EVERYONE TRUSTS YOU NOW?

92
00:06:49,125 --> 00:06:51,333
I WAS THE FIRST PERSON
TO TRUST YOU, REMEMBER?

93
00:06:51,375 --> 00:06:53,208
BACK IN BA SING SE.

94
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:56,625
AND YOU TURNED AROUND AND
BETRAYED ME, BETRAYED ALL OF US.

95
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:59,333
WHAT CAN I DO
TO MAKE IT UP TO YOU?

96
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:01,375
YOU REALLY WANT TO KNOW?

97
00:07:01,417 --> 00:07:05,166
HMM, MAYBE YOU COULD
RECONQUER BA SING SE
IN THE NAME OF THE EARTH KING.

98
00:07:05,208 --> 00:07:07,959
OR, I KNOW, YOU COULD
BRING MY MOTHER BACK.

99
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:17,417
OOPS.

100
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:19,125
WRONG TENT.

101
00:07:19,166 --> 00:07:21,875
SORRY, DO YOU NEED TO
TALK TO SOKKA TOO?

102
00:07:21,917 --> 00:07:24,375
NOPE, NOT ME.

103
00:07:27,083 --> 00:07:30,417
WELL, HELLO.

104
00:07:30,458 --> 00:07:34,375
UH, ZUKO, YES, WHY WOULD I BE
EXPECTING ANYONE DIFFERENT?

105
00:07:34,417 --> 00:07:36,500
[GULPS, COUGHS]

106
00:07:36,542 --> 00:07:38,667
SO WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

107
00:07:38,709 --> 00:07:41,750
YOUR SISTER, SHE HATES ME,
AND I DON'T KNOW WHY.

108
00:07:41,792 --> 00:07:44,083
BUT I DO CARE
WHAT SHE THINKS OF ME.

109
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:46,000
NAH, SHE DOESN'T HATE YOU.

110
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:47,959
KATARA DOESN'T HATE ANYONE.

111
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,083
EXCEPT MAYBE SOME PEOPLE
IN THE FIRE NATION.

112
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:53,959
NO, I MEAN, UH, NOT PEOPLE
WHO ARE GOOD BUT USED TO BE BAD.

113
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,250
I MEAN BAD PEOPLE.

114
00:07:56,291 --> 00:07:59,291
FIRE NATION PEOPLE WHO ARE STILL
BAD, WHO'VE NEVER BEEN GOOD
AND PROBABLY WON'T BE EVER.

115
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:00,709
STOP.

116
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:02,834
OK, LISTEN...

117
00:08:02,875 --> 00:08:05,041
I KNOW THIS MAY SEEM
OUT OF NOWHERE

118
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:07,583
BUT I WANT YOU TO TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR MOTHER.

119
00:08:07,625 --> 00:08:08,583
WHAT?

120
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:10,750
WHY WOULD YOU WANT TO KNOW THAT?

121
00:08:10,792 --> 00:08:13,750
KATARA MENTIONED IT BEFORE
WHEN WE WERE IN PRISON TOGETHER
IN BA SING SE

122
00:08:13,792 --> 00:08:16,250
AND AGAIN JUST NOW
WHEN SHE WAS YELLING AT ME.

123
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:18,667
I THINK SOMEHOW...

124
00:08:18,709 --> 00:08:22,709
SHE'S CONNECTED HER ANGER
ABOUT THAT TO HER ANGER AT ME.

125
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:25,000
IT'S NOT A DAY
I LIKE TO REMEMBER.

126
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:34,375
[LAUGHING]

127
00:08:39,458 --> 00:08:42,125
I'M GOING TO FIND MOM.

128
00:08:44,625 --> 00:08:47,417
Sokka: MANY OF THE WARRIORS HAD
SEEN THE BLACK SNOW BEFORE

129
00:08:47,458 --> 00:08:49,208
AND THEY KNEW WHAT IT MEANT...

130
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:51,125
A FIRE NATION RAID.

131
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:52,959
[SCREAMING]

132
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:57,875
[SCREAMING]

133
00:09:01,917 --> 00:09:05,458
Sokka: WE WERE BADLY
OUTNUMBERED, BUT SOMEHOW
WE MANAGED TO DRIVE THEM OFF.

134
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:12,750
AS QUICKLY AS THEY CAME,
THEY JUST LEFT.

135
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,667
I WAS SO RELIEVED
WHEN IT WAS OVER

136
00:09:18,709 --> 00:09:21,917
BUT THAT'S BECAUSE I DIDN'T
KNOW YET WHAT HAD HAPPENED.

137
00:09:21,959 --> 00:09:24,375
I DIDN'T KNOW
WE'D LOST OUR MOTHER.

138
00:09:24,417 --> 00:09:28,709
WAIT, CAN YOU REMEMBER
ANY DETAILS ABOUT THE SOLDIERS
WHO RAIDED YOUR VILLAGE?

139
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:31,333
LIKE WHAT THE LEAD SHIP
LOOKED LIKE?

140
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:33,834
YEAH... SEA RAVENS.

141
00:09:33,875 --> 00:09:36,875
THE MAIN SHIP HAD FLAGS
WITH SEA RAVENS ON THEM.

142
00:09:36,917 --> 00:09:39,041
THE SYMBOL OF
THE SOUTHERN RAIDERS.

143
00:09:39,083 --> 00:09:40,458
THANKS, SOKKA.

144
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,834
NO PROBLEM.

145
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:44,875
THANKS FOR STOPPING BY.

146
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:48,041
[SIGHS] THOUGHT
HE'D NEVER LEAVE.

147
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:51,083
SUKI?

148
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:54,166
[WHISTLING]

149
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:03,500
YOU LOOK TERRIBLE.

150
00:10:03,542 --> 00:10:05,583
I WAITED OUT HERE ALL NIGHT.

151
00:10:05,625 --> 00:10:07,333
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

152
00:10:07,375 --> 00:10:09,250
I KNOW WHO KILLED YOUR MOTHER.

153
00:10:09,291 --> 00:10:10,542
I'M GOING TO HELP YOU FIND HIM.

154
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:21,166
I NEED TO BORROW APPA.

155
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:24,208
WHY, IS IT YOUR TURN TO TAKE
A LITTLE FIELD TRIP WITH ZUKO?

156
00:10:24,250 --> 00:10:27,333
YES, IT IS.

157
00:10:27,375 --> 00:10:29,917
OH... WHAT'S GOING ON?

158
00:10:29,959 --> 00:10:32,709
WE'RE GOING TO FIND THE MAN
WHO TOOK MY MOTHER FROM ME.

159
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:35,000
Zuko: SOKKA TOLD ME
THE STORY OF WHAT HAPPENED.

160
00:10:35,041 --> 00:10:38,166
I KNOW WHO DID IT,
AND I KNOW HOW TO FIND HIM.

161
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:41,667
UM, AND WHAT EXACTLY DO YOU
THINK THIS WILL ACCOMPLISH?

162
00:10:41,709 --> 00:10:44,667
[SCOFFS] I KNEW
YOU WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND.

163
00:10:44,709 --> 00:10:47,834
WAIT, STOP, I DO UNDERSTAND.

164
00:10:47,875 --> 00:10:50,583
YOU'RE FEELING UNBELIEVABLE
PAIN AND RAGE.

165
00:10:50,625 --> 00:10:54,667
HOW DO YOU THINK I FELT
ABOUT THE SANDBENDERS
WHEN THEY STOLE APPA?

166
00:10:54,709 --> 00:10:58,458
HOW DO YOU THINK I FELT ABOUT
THE FIRE NATION WHEN I FOUND OUT
WHAT HAPPENED TO MY PEOPLE?

167
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,959
Zuko: SHE NEEDS THIS, AANG.

168
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,667
THIS IS ABOUT GETTING CLOSURE
AND JUSTICE.

169
00:11:02,709 --> 00:11:04,041
I DON'T THINK SO.

170
00:11:04,083 --> 00:11:05,917
I THINK IT'S ABOUT
GETTING REVENGE.

171
00:11:05,959 --> 00:11:07,250
Katara: FINE, MAYBE IT IS.

172
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:09,166
MAYBE THAT'S WHAT I NEED.

173
00:11:09,208 --> 00:11:11,417
MAYBE THAT'S WHAT HE DESERVES.

174
00:11:11,458 --> 00:11:13,542
KATARA, YOU SOUND LIKE JET.

175
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:15,041
IT'S NOT THE SAME.

176
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:16,458
JET ATTACKED THE INNOCENT.

177
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,709
THIS MAN, HE'S A MONSTER.

178
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,625
KATARA, SHE WAS MY MOTHER TOO.

179
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:23,333
BUT I THINK AANG MIGHT BE RIGHT.

180
00:11:23,375 --> 00:11:25,291
THEN YOU DIDN'T LOVE HER
THE WAY I DID.

181
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:26,625
KATARA...

182
00:11:28,583 --> 00:11:32,417
THE MONKS USED TO SAY
THAT REVENGE IS LIKE
A TWO-HEADED RAT VIPER.

183
00:11:32,458 --> 00:11:35,875
WHILE YOU WATCH YOUR ENEMY
GO DOWN, YOU'RE BEING
POISONED YOURSELF.

184
00:11:35,917 --> 00:11:38,709
THAT'S CUTE, BUT THIS ISN'T
AIR TEMPLE PRESCHOOL.

185
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:40,750
IT'S THE REAL WORLD.

186
00:11:40,792 --> 00:11:42,542
NOW THAT I KNOW
HE'S OUT THERE...

187
00:11:42,583 --> 00:11:44,500
NOW THAT I KNOW
WE CAN FIND HIM...

188
00:11:44,542 --> 00:11:46,500
I FEEL LIKE I HAVE NO CHOICE.

189
00:11:46,542 --> 00:11:49,041
KATARA, YOU DO HAVE A CHOICE.

190
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,625
FORGIVENESS.

191
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:52,583
THAT'S THE SAME AS
DOING NOTHING.

192
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:54,500
NO, IT'S NOT.

193
00:11:54,542 --> 00:11:58,583
IT'S EASY TO DO NOTHING,
BUT IT'S HARD TO FORGIVE.

194
00:11:58,625 --> 00:12:02,667
IT'S NOT JUST HARD,
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

195
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:14,667
SO YOU WERE JUST GONNA
TAKE APPA ANYWAY?

196
00:12:14,709 --> 00:12:16,542
YES.

197
00:12:16,583 --> 00:12:19,917
IT'S OK, BECAUSE I FORGIVE YOU.

198
00:12:19,959 --> 00:12:22,166
THAT GIVE YOU ANY IDEAS?

199
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:23,792
DON'T TRY TO STOP US.

200
00:12:23,834 --> 00:12:25,625
I WASN'T PLANNING TO.

201
00:12:25,667 --> 00:12:27,542
THIS IS A JOURNEY
YOU NEED TO TAKE.

202
00:12:27,583 --> 00:12:29,375
YOU NEED TO FACE THIS MAN.

203
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:35,000
BUT WHEN YOU DO,
PLEASE DON'T CHOOSE REVENGE.

204
00:12:35,041 --> 00:12:38,041
LET YOUR ANGER OUT,
AND THEN LET IT GO.

205
00:12:38,083 --> 00:12:40,041
FORGIVE HIM.

206
00:12:40,083 --> 00:12:43,375
OK, WE'LL BE SURE TO DO THAT,
GURU GOODY-GOODY.

207
00:12:43,417 --> 00:12:45,000
- THANKS FOR UNDERSTANDING,
AANG.

208
00:12:45,041 --> 00:12:47,291
YIP-YIP.

209
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:48,750
[APPA GROANING]

210
00:12:48,792 --> 00:12:50,625
- YOU KNOW, YOU'RE PRETTY WISE
FOR A KID.

211
00:12:50,667 --> 00:12:52,208
- THANKS, SOKKA.

212
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:54,625
USUALLY IT'S ANNOYING, BUT
RIGHT NOW I'M JUST IMPRESSED.

213
00:12:54,667 --> 00:12:56,291
I APPRECIATE THAT.

214
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,417
SO CAN I BORROW MOMO FOR A WEEK?

215
00:12:58,458 --> 00:12:59,625
WHY DO YOU NEED MOMO?

216
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:00,834
[HUMS]: I DON'T KNOW.

217
00:13:04,041 --> 00:13:07,250
Zuko: WE NEED TO FIND THE
FIRE NAVY COMMUNICATION TOWER.

218
00:13:07,291 --> 00:13:10,291
ALL THE NAVY'S MOVEMENTS ARE
COORDINATED BY MESSENGER HAWK

219
00:13:10,333 --> 00:13:13,917
AND EVERY TOWER
HAS TO BE UP TO DATE
ON WHERE EVERYONE IS DEPLOYED.

220
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:15,917
Katara: SO ONCE WE FIND
THE COMMUNICATION TOWER

221
00:13:15,959 --> 00:13:18,166
WE BUST IN AND TAKE
THE INFORMATION WE NEED.

222
00:13:18,208 --> 00:13:20,000
Zuko: NOT EXACTLY.

223
00:13:20,041 --> 00:13:23,333
WE NEED TO BE STEALTHY
AND MAKE SURE NO ONE SPOTS US.

224
00:13:23,375 --> 00:13:26,542
OTHERWISE, THEY'LL WARN
THE SOUTHERN RAIDERS
LONG BEFORE WE REACH THEM.

225
00:13:35,750 --> 00:13:38,667
[DOOR CREAKS]

226
00:13:52,041 --> 00:13:54,500
OK, SOUTHERN RAIDERS.

227
00:13:57,375 --> 00:14:00,542
BAM, ON PATROL
NEAR WHALE TAIL ISLAND.

228
00:14:00,583 --> 00:14:03,875
WHALE TAIL ISLAND,
HERE WE COME.

229
00:14:03,917 --> 00:14:06,250
[APPA GROANS]

230
00:14:11,583 --> 00:14:13,083
YOU SHOULD GET SOME REST.

231
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:14,500
WE'LL BE THERE IN A FEW HOURS.

232
00:14:14,542 --> 00:14:16,667
YOU'LL NEED ALL YOUR STRENGTH.

233
00:14:16,709 --> 00:14:18,500
OH, DON'T YOU WORRY
ABOUT MY STRENGTH.

234
00:14:18,542 --> 00:14:20,083
I HAVE PLENTY.

235
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:22,667
I'M NOT THE HELPLESS LITTLE GIRL
I WAS WHEN THEY CAME.

236
00:14:26,417 --> 00:14:29,125
I'M GOING TO FIND MOM.

237
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:33,875
MOM!

238
00:14:35,417 --> 00:14:37,709
Mother: JUST LET HER GO...

239
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:40,083
AND I'LL GIVE YOU
THE INFORMATION YOU WANT.

240
00:14:40,125 --> 00:14:42,542
YOU HEARD YOUR MOTHER...
GET OUT OF HERE!

241
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:44,542
MOM, I'M SCARED.

242
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:46,083
GO FIND YOUR DAD, SWEETIE.

243
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:47,250
I'LL HANDLE THIS.

244
00:14:54,792 --> 00:14:56,959
Katara: I RAN
AS FAST AS I COULD.

245
00:14:57,041 --> 00:14:58,792
DAD, DAD!

246
00:14:58,834 --> 00:15:01,000
PLEASE, I THINK MOM'S
IN TROUBLE!

247
00:15:01,041 --> 00:15:02,083
THERE'S A MAN IN OUR HOUSE.

248
00:15:02,125 --> 00:15:03,417
KYA!

249
00:15:07,709 --> 00:15:09,625
Katara: BUT WE WERE TOO LATE.

250
00:15:09,667 --> 00:15:12,125
WHEN WE GOT THERE,
THE MAN WAS GONE...

251
00:15:12,166 --> 00:15:13,375
AND SO WAS SHE.

252
00:15:13,417 --> 00:15:15,750
YOUR MOTHER WAS A BRAVE WOMAN.

253
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:19,417
I KNOW.

254
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:27,625
THERE, SEE THOSE
SEA RAVEN FLAGS?

255
00:15:31,208 --> 00:15:32,917
Zuko: IT'S THE SOUTHERN RAIDERS.

256
00:15:32,959 --> 00:15:34,583
LET'S DO THIS.

257
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:44,333
SO THERE I WAS, AND I WAS LIKE,
YOU KNOW, IT WAS...

258
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:46,542
[SCREAMS]

259
00:15:57,917 --> 00:15:58,709
[SCREAMING]

260
00:16:01,834 --> 00:16:04,917
[APPA SNORTS]

261
00:16:04,959 --> 00:16:07,625
[SCREAMS]

262
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:12,750
[MAN GRUNTS]

263
00:16:16,583 --> 00:16:18,333
THIS IS IT, KATARA.

264
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:19,875
ARE YOU READY TO FACE HIM?

265
00:16:22,875 --> 00:16:26,875
[ROARS]

266
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:35,417
WHO ARE YOU?

267
00:16:35,458 --> 00:16:37,000
YOU DON'T REMEMBER HER?

268
00:16:37,041 --> 00:16:38,792
YOU WILL SOON, TRUST ME.

269
00:16:42,542 --> 00:16:43,834
WHAT'S...

270
00:16:43,875 --> 00:16:46,208
[GRUNTING]

271
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:47,834
HAPPENING TO ME?

272
00:16:49,417 --> 00:16:51,000
[GROANS]

273
00:16:54,125 --> 00:16:56,166
THINK BACK.

274
00:16:56,208 --> 00:16:58,667
THINK BACK TO YOUR LAST RAID
ON THE SOUTHERN WATER TRIBE.

275
00:16:58,709 --> 00:17:00,750
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

276
00:17:00,792 --> 00:17:02,500
PLEASE, I DON'T KNOW.

277
00:17:02,542 --> 00:17:04,583
DON'T LIE!

278
00:17:04,625 --> 00:17:07,208
YOU LOOK HER IN THE EYE
AND YOU TELL ME YOU DON'T
REMEMBER WHAT YOU DID.

279
00:17:16,834 --> 00:17:18,542
IT'S NOT HIM.

280
00:17:20,083 --> 00:17:21,375
[GRUNTS]

281
00:17:21,417 --> 00:17:22,709
HE'S NOT THE MAN.

282
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:23,750
WHAT?

283
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:25,291
WHAT DO YOU MEAN HE'S NOT?

284
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:26,917
HE'S THE LEADER OF
THE SOUTHERN RAIDERS.

285
00:17:26,959 --> 00:17:28,291
HE HAS TO BE THE GUY.

286
00:17:33,667 --> 00:17:35,250
[GRUNTING]

287
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:37,041
IF YOU'RE NOT THE MAN
WE'RE LOOKING FOR, WHO IS?

288
00:17:37,083 --> 00:17:39,166
YOU MUST BE LOOKING FOR YON RHA.

289
00:17:39,208 --> 00:17:42,125
HE RETIRED FOUR YEARS AGO.

290
00:17:52,792 --> 00:17:57,250
YON RHA, YOU LAZY PIECE OF WORK,
I NEED SOMETHING.

291
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:59,333
YES, MOTHER.

292
00:17:59,375 --> 00:18:00,917
WHAT IS IT?

293
00:18:00,959 --> 00:18:04,083
THE TOMATO-CARROT FROM YOUR
GARDEN ARE TOO HARD FOR MY GUMS.

294
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:06,917
I NEED SOMETHING SOFT AND JUICY.

295
00:18:06,959 --> 00:18:09,667
WOULD YOU LIKE SOMETHING ELSE
FROM THE GARDEN?

296
00:18:09,709 --> 00:18:10,959
I WOULD BE HAPPY TO...

297
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,250
FORGET YOUR STUPID GARDEN!

298
00:18:13,291 --> 00:18:16,667
GET YOUR GRIMY HEINIE
TO THE MARKET AND BUY ME
SOME REAL FOOD.

299
00:18:19,917 --> 00:18:23,583
[THUNDER RUMBLING FAINTLY]

300
00:18:23,625 --> 00:18:26,500
[WIND CHIMES RINGING...]

301
00:18:32,542 --> 00:18:34,250
HELLO?

302
00:18:34,291 --> 00:18:37,000
DID YOU SEE SOMEONE?

303
00:18:45,542 --> 00:18:47,709
HELLO?

304
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:48,917
IS SOMEONE THERE?

305
00:18:52,083 --> 00:18:53,417
THAT WAS HIM.

306
00:18:53,458 --> 00:18:55,083
THAT WAS THE MONSTER.

307
00:19:00,417 --> 00:19:03,041
[THUNDER RUMBLING...]

308
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:10,166
NOBODY SNEAKS UP ON ME
WITHOUT GETTING BURNED.

309
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:23,208
[GRUNTS]

310
00:19:27,959 --> 00:19:30,041
WE WEREN'T BEHIND THE BUSH.

311
00:19:30,083 --> 00:19:33,709
AND I WOULDN'T TRY
FIREBENDING AGAIN.

312
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:36,959
WHOEVER YOU ARE, TAKE MY MONEY,
TAKE WHATEVER YOU WANT.

313
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,250
I'LL COOPERATE.

314
00:19:39,291 --> 00:19:41,792
DO YOU KNOW WHO I AM?

315
00:19:41,834 --> 00:19:45,125
NO... I'M NOT SURE.

316
00:19:45,166 --> 00:19:47,959
OH, YOU BETTER REMEMBER ME
LIKE YOUR LIFE DEPENDS ON IT.

317
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:50,291
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE
A CLOSER LOOK?

318
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:54,917
YES, YES, I REMEMBER YOU NOW.

319
00:19:54,959 --> 00:19:57,375
YOU'RE THE LITTLE
WATER TRIBE GIRL.

320
00:19:57,417 --> 00:19:59,166
[THUNDER CRASHES]

321
00:19:59,208 --> 00:20:01,875
JUST LET HER GO AND I'LL GIVE
YOU THE INFORMATION YOU WANT.

322
00:20:01,917 --> 00:20:03,458
YOU HEARD YOUR MOTHER.

323
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:05,375
GET OUT OF HERE.

324
00:20:05,417 --> 00:20:07,250
MOM, I'M SCARED.

325
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:08,792
GO FIND YOUR DAD, SWEETIE.

326
00:20:08,834 --> 00:20:10,667
I'LL HANDLE THIS.

327
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:17,000
NOW TELL ME...
WHO IS IT?

328
00:20:17,041 --> 00:20:19,000
WHO'S THE WATERBENDER?

329
00:20:19,041 --> 00:20:21,667
THERE ARE NO WATERBENDERS HERE.

330
00:20:21,709 --> 00:20:24,834
THE FIRE NATION TOOK THEM
ALL AWAY A LONG TIME AGO.

331
00:20:24,875 --> 00:20:27,000
YOU'RE LYING.

332
00:20:27,041 --> 00:20:31,375
MY SOURCE SAYS
THERE'S ONE WATERBENDER LEFT
IN THE SOUTHERN WATER TRIBE.

333
00:20:31,417 --> 00:20:35,125
WE'RE NOT LEAVING
UNTIL WE FIND THE WATERBENDER.

334
00:20:35,166 --> 00:20:38,917
IF I TELL YOU, DO YOU PROMISE
TO LEAVE THE REST OF
THE VILLAGE ALONE?

335
00:20:38,959 --> 00:20:41,250
MM.

336
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:44,875
IT'S ME... TAKE ME
AS YOUR PRISONER.

337
00:20:44,917 --> 00:20:48,250
I'M AFRAID I'M NOT
TAKING PRISONERS TODAY.

338
00:20:50,208 --> 00:20:51,250
[GULPS]

339
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:52,750
[THUNDER CRASHES]

340
00:20:52,792 --> 00:20:54,083
SHE LIED TO YOU.

341
00:20:54,125 --> 00:20:56,458
SHE WAS PROTECTING
THE LAST WATERBENDER.

342
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,375
WHAT?

343
00:20:57,417 --> 00:20:59,417
WHO?

344
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:02,208
ME!

345
00:21:13,583 --> 00:21:16,458
[GRUNTS]

346
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:19,166
[WHIMPERS]

347
00:21:30,208 --> 00:21:34,500
I DID A BAD THING, I KNOW I DID,
AND YOU DESERVE REVENGE.

348
00:21:34,542 --> 00:21:36,834
SO WHY DON'T YOU TAKE MY MOTHER?

349
00:21:36,875 --> 00:21:38,500
THAT WOULD BE FAIR.

350
00:21:38,542 --> 00:21:42,000
I ALWAYS WONDERED WHAT KIND OF
PERSON COULD DO SUCH A THING.

351
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:45,333
BUT NOW THAT I SEE YOU,
I THINK I UNDERSTAND.

352
00:21:45,375 --> 00:21:49,083
THERE'S JUST NOTHING INSIDE YOU,
NOTHING AT ALL.

353
00:21:49,125 --> 00:21:51,667
YOU'RE PATHETIC AND SAD
AND EMPTY.

354
00:21:51,709 --> 00:21:54,417
PLEASE SPARE ME. [WHIMPERS]

355
00:21:54,458 --> 00:21:57,834
BUT AS MUCH AS I HATE YOU...

356
00:21:57,875 --> 00:21:59,792
I JUST CAN'T DO IT.

357
00:22:06,417 --> 00:22:09,250
[YON RHA WHIMPERING...]

358
00:22:19,667 --> 00:22:20,875
[APPA GROANS]

359
00:22:27,458 --> 00:22:29,583
KATARA, ARE YOU OK?

360
00:22:29,625 --> 00:22:32,667
- I'M DOING FINE.

361
00:22:32,709 --> 00:22:34,959
ZUKO TOLD ME WHAT YOU DID.

362
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,333
OR WHAT YOU DIDN'T DO, I GUESS.

363
00:22:37,375 --> 00:22:38,792
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

364
00:22:38,834 --> 00:22:41,125
I WANTED TO DO IT.

365
00:22:41,166 --> 00:22:45,375
I WANTED TO TAKE OUT ALL MY
ANGER AT HIM, BUT I COULDN'T.

366
00:22:45,417 --> 00:22:50,458
I DON'T KNOW IF IT'S
BECAUSE I'M TOO WEAK TO DO IT OR
IF IT'S BECAUSE I'M STRONG
ENOUGH NOT TO.

367
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:52,333
Aang: YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

368
00:22:52,375 --> 00:22:57,750
FORGIVENESS IS THE FIRST STEP
YOU HAVE TO TAKE
TO BEGIN HEALING.

369
00:22:57,792 --> 00:23:02,542
BUT I DIDN'T FORGIVE HIM...
I'LL NEVER FORGIVE HIM.

370
00:23:02,583 --> 00:23:05,000
BUT I AM READY TO FORGIVE YOU.

371
00:23:12,125 --> 00:23:14,875
Zuko: YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT WHAT KATARA NEEDED.

372
00:23:14,917 --> 00:23:16,875
VIOLENCE WASN'T THE ANSWER.

373
00:23:16,917 --> 00:23:18,834
IT NEVER IS.

374
00:23:18,875 --> 00:23:21,917
THEN I HAVE A QUESTION FOR YOU.

375
00:23:21,959 --> 00:23:24,125
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
WHEN YOU FACE MY FATHER?

376
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:39,000
♪
